  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthened Member states capacity to sustainably manage natural resources and sustainable economic and social development through UNESCO Global Geoparks</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">LAC is facing increasing conflicts related to the exploitation of natural resources and raw materials in a context of climate change and rising population, changing lifestyles increasing demand for raw materials. In support of a more equitable LAC, where no one is left behind, following sustainable and inclusive development path, UNESCO Montevideo will promote generation and sharing of knowledge in relation to natural resource uses, capacity for the protection, sustainable and rational management of the Earth&apos;s geological resources through UNESCO Global Geoparks. Also supporting education in Earth Sciences, promoting decision making cross-sector dialogue on the development agenda, and creating new Global UNESCO Geoparks as platforms for sustainable development through geotourism.</narrative>
  </description>
